channel.title: Need Help... Again
channel.description:
Seems every time I try to mess around with private servers I always have the same issues on start up. With my new laptop I have been unable to run certain clients/servers and no compiler has worked. Currently my values are:
[ul][li]Classpath:C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin [/li] [li]Path:C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin[/li][/ul]
Can anyone send me their values and maybe a compiler or run.bat? I've tried NUMEROUS different ones already and non have worked. I am operating on windows 7.
And please no dick responses I'll admit now without hesitation that I'm a narble supreme who knows very little if any at all about coding but would like to learn, thank you.

item.title: Need Help... Again
item.dc:creator: @the_elve_age the elve age
item.description:
@the_elve_age wrote:

Why would this work for you? Do you even know what that code is?

Read it bro - go to the disk drive C:/Program Files

Is your computer an x86, if not remove it.

Go to the java folder under C:/Program Files; you should see a file that says “jdk1.X.X_X”

Just replace what that jdk folder is called with the ones you have up there and it should be fine.
